column5: You just need to go where trophy musky are common....  I've heard of so many 50"+ fish in the past 3 weeks it's crazy...
Beauty. Were you fishing in the dark? Or did the flash just make it look that late?
No worries.   Still quite the impressive catch.
nice fish; congrats

wow... old fish, but still in here prime.  Looks like a Simcoe strain for sure.  Im going to say somewhere between cooch and Glouster pool area?  was talking about the 54"er  2 beauties in this thread for sure
That was midnight during a major bite window... Full moon fish...
Great fish! Still trying for my first 50"er, got to get out more.
Great fish for both of you!!
Monster fish. Congrats !!!
That's a dragon! Nice stuff gettin into the 50"+ Way to go!
Congrats to Brian White AKA Ugly bug....  He landed this 50.5" st lawrence beauty last night....
Damn nice fish !!!!
beauti thick fish.  Congrats!

Nice fish for your buddy !Not to highjack your thread , but my buddy ( WeedLine from the board here )caught this beauty 54" ski from an inland lake. his PB muskyneedless to say that I am proud of him but a little jealous
Great fish and a somewhat difficult milestone to reach.   I keep falling one inch too short.   Got two upcoming trips to try again.   Congrats to the anglers if course
The classic line everyone uses before they completely high jack a thread by posting something that completely outdoes the original post...  Lol
Very nice fish by both guys.
I'll take either, or both. Congrats to both anglers.
Congrats to both guys for some nice skis
Great fish.  Thanks for putting the pics up.
Mike catch a bigger one to raise the bar.
Awesome fish tho
Sorry Mike. I know my buddy wont post his pic. I guess if that's highjacking , Im guilty as charged LOL

No biggy...  It's just funny how people say things like that... Lol  I got a 54" PB this year as well... Still trying to break the 55"+ club... It's coming....  Buddy put a 56" in the boat a week or 2 ago...
Congrats Brian well done
Wow, both beasts! The 54" is a mean looking creature, very dark colours.
Also great fish for both,must be something to catch a fish that big.Maybe one day lol.Still trying to beat my 42" pike a while back..
Very nice fish indeed !!
High jack,smack jack.  You musky guys are too much.  Atleast us steelheader get along.  Great two fish by both anglers.
Absolute monsters nice job to the both of you, I can only dream of catching one of those at this point (at least until September when I go to lake st clair that is haha)
Who are you trying to kid...... LOL!!!  Both nice fish!!
Woohoooo, nice!!!
Sorry guys. I was wrong. my buddys fish was 52.5 not 54
A couple monsters, but this thing looks like a lurking beast.
I keep falling one inch too short. Got two upcoming trips to try again.  Got my fingers crossed for you this year Rich, your due for sure.
